	   <tr><td colspan=2>"Considering how you obviously have a hard time grasping the concept of the EQ-term 'farming' and what it truly means, let me spell it out for you: farming is working the same mobs over in rapid sucession for multiple respawns, in order to increase the chances of obtaining favorable drops. "<br><br>Not to take sides here but you described sounds more like "camping" than "farming".  I understand "farming" to be clearing "green" mobs for their drop, usually marked by NOT taking other than the item(s) you are looking for.  For example killing bats for wings, and leaving the fur or junk armour.<br><br>I could be mistaken, but that is my understanding.<br><br>Now, more on topic, yes they look as though they would be a very nice pair of gloves for my ENC.<br><br>&nbsp;<br></td></tr>
